Prereqs: elasticsearch, git

0) Get the code:
     git clone git://github.com/mateu/Git-Search.git

1) Copy git-search.conf to git-search-local.conf and edit it to your needs.
   This means adapting the configuration to point to your elasticsearch
   service and the git repo you want to search.

2) Create index (with debug on to see the files used), execute:
     GIT_SEARCH_DEBUG=1 perl -Ilib bin/insert_docs.pl  

3) Start app, execute:
     plackup -Ilib 

4) Do a search by requesting:  http://localhost:5000/search phrase
